Steepening the absorption edge for reduced photon energy losses with strong coupling. a Sensitively measured EQE spectra of the investigated SubNc/Cl6-PhOSubPc based SC-devices for various transport layer thicknesses d, including the reference solar cell employing only SubNc (‘SubNc’). Increasing d red-shifts the device absorption, steepening the absorption edge. b Urbach energy (EU) versus Eg–qVOC losses for the SubNc/Cl6-PhOSubPc based SC-device (‘SC-SubNc’), exhibiting the EU = 15.6 meV and energy losses of 0.525 eV, and record solar cells of other inorganic photovoltaic technologies. The reference SubNc/Cl6-PhOSubPc device (‘SubNc’) is also included to demonstrate how strong coupling reduces both EU and photon energy losses. Adapted by De Wolf et al. 33 and Jean et al. 36. cEU values for various organic photovoltaic materials and blends. The value of 15.6 meV for the ‘SC-SubNc’ device is the lowest for organic materials. Values of materials and blends, which were not investigated in this work, were taken from literature34,37–40
